Overview
--------
The TQMLS1088A SOM is a high-performance computing platform that supports the
QorIQ LS1088A LayerScape Architecture processor.

LS1088A SoC Overview
--------------------
Please refer arch/arm/cpu/armv8/fsl-layerscape/doc/README.soc for LS1088A
SoC overview.

TQMLS1088A board Overview
------------------------
 - SERDES Connections, 8 lanes supporting:
      - PCI Express - 3.0
      - SGMII, SGMII 2.5
      - QSGMII
      - SATA 3.0
      - XFI
 - DDR Controller:
     - 2GB 64bits DDR4 SDRAM. Support rates of up to 2133MT/s
 - USB 3.0:
    - Two high speed USB 3.0 ports
 - SDHC:
    - eMMC memory devices
    - alternative SD slot for SD, SDHC (1x, 4x) on baseboard
 - DSPI:
    - Onboard support for two SPI flash memory devices
 - 4 I2C controllers
 - ARM JTAG support

Note: XFI function depends on correct initialization by U-Boot. It will
not work as expected when booting into an OS kernel directly from SPL
("Falcon Mode").

Memory map from core's view
----------------------------
Start Address    End Address     Description        Size
0x00_0000_0000 - 0x00_000F_FFFF  Secure Boot ROM    1MB
0x00_0100_0000 - 0x00_0FFF_FFFF  CCSRBAR            240MB
0x00_1800_0000 - 0x00_181F_FFFF  OCRAM              2MB
0x00_8000_0000 - 0x00_FFFF_FFFF  DRAM               2GB
0x07_0000_0000 - 0x07_3FFF_FFFF  DCSR               1GB
0x08_0C00_0000 - 0x08_0FFF_FFFF  MC S/W Portals     64MB
0x08_1800_0000 - 0x08_1FFF_FFFF  QBMAN S/W Portal   128MB
0x20_0000_0000 - 0x27_FFFF_FFFF  PCI Express1       32G
0x28_0000_0000 - 0x2F_FFFF_FFFF  PCI Express2       32G
0x30_0000_0000 - 0x37_FFFF_FFFF  PCI Express3       32G

QSPI flash map:
Start Address    End Address     Description	    Size
0x00_4000_0000 - 0x00_4000_FFFF  RCW,PBI            64KB
0x00_4001_0000 - 0x00_400C_FFFF  U-Boot             768KB
0x00_400D_0000 - 0x00_400D_FFFF  U-Boot Env         64KB
0x00_400E_0000 - 0x00_400E_FFFF  DPAA2 MC DPL       64KB
0x00_400F_0000 - 0x00_400F_FFFF  DPAA2 MC DPC       64KB
0x00_4010_0000 - 0x00_402E_FFFF  DPAA2 MC Microcode 1984KB
0x00_402F_0000 - 0x00_402F_FFFF  Linux device-tree  64KB
0x00_4030_0000 - 0x00_417F_FFFF  Linux Image        21MB
0x00_4180_0000 - 0x00_43FF_FFFF  Linux UBI rootfs   40MB

Booting Options
---------------
a) QSPI boot
b) SD boot
c) eMMC boot
